The dev setup on M-series chips and MacOS needs some extra work, unfornately it doesn't work out of the box (like Nix does). I know people have some trouble with it, but I managed to get it to work on my machine - here's what I shared internally, maybe this will help you 


> I have received many messages over the last few days regarding building Mina (more specifically the o1js bindings that require Mina) on MacBooks with M-series chips. So, I took some time to sit down and debug my build locally to get it working natively without Nix.
> 
> My setup: M3 Pro, Sonoma 14.1.1
> 
> A few pointers:
> - You will need to ping a repository that hosts a back ported fix for async_ssl  
>    - opam pin add async_ssl https://github.com/Trivo25/async_ssl.git#v0.14
> - Make sure gmp 6.2.1 is installed on your device, you can do that manually via https://gmplib.org/manual/Installing-GMP
>    - Why not just brew? Looks like it doesn't host that specific version anymore
> - Other than that, following the dev-README in the Mina repository closely should solve all remaining issues


> More specifically, for building the o1js bindings, you will need the GNU version of sed, because the MacOS sed behaves differently.
> https://www.gnu.org/software/sed/
